  Adaon turns toward a rack on the wall behind him, and lifts an 
instrument from it.  He says, "This be a >lute<, me friend, the symbol 
of what it is t' be a bard.  It's an invaluable tool for our profession.  
Mark me words, if you join the >bards< and lose y'r >lute<, y'll find 
y'rsel' nigh helpless.  O' course, if ye come back here, I can get ye 
another one.  Always have a few extras about, for in my younger 
days, when I wooed women wi' me >music< and braved the world 
>fighting< impossible dangers, I managed to lose mine occasionally.  
Twas nae a fun thing, let me tell you.
  "Most o' a bard's >talents< are derived from the >lute<.  It allows 
much greater expression o' y'rsel' than mere speech or song alone 
does."

  A bard may also play single clear notes on the lute with:

     play lute <note>

  Available notes are C4 D4 E4 F4 G4 A4 B4 C5 D5 E5 F5 G5 A5 B5 C6.
Those nearby may hear the note through Darkflow if their sound is enabled.
